FBIS4-41386 "drsov122_h_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Moldova Dniester Leader Says Only Russians Can Keep Peace Dniester Leader Says Only Russians Can Keep Peace LD2306203194 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1940 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306203194 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] If UN troops come into the Dniester region they will not be perceived by the population as peacekeepers. This was said at a news conference today by Igor Smirnov, president of the Dniester-Moldavia [Moldova] Republic. Speaking about the results of the conference of international cooperation in peacekeeping in regions of conflict on the territory of the CIS, which was held in Moscow from 20-22 June, he expressed the firm conviction that only Russia has the right to peacekeeping activities in the Dniester region.
